org.codeoverflow.chatoverflow.api.plugin.configuration

Class Requirements

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.codeoverflow.chatoverflow.api.plugin.configuration.Requirements

  • public class Requirements
extends java.lang.Object
    A requirements object is used to hold all needed parameters and connections of a plugin. The specific values can be required in the input, output and parameter objects.

      • getAccess

        public Requirements.RequirementsAccessor getAccess()
                                            throws java.lang.SecurityException
        Retrieves the Accessor for write privileges on requirements. Please note, that this function is only legal to call in the framework, not inside your plugins code.
        Returns:
        the requirement accessor with utility functions on requirements
        Throws:
        java.lang.SecurityException - thrown when used from inside a plugin
